 <span data-ttu-id="538f6-444">识别器设置可以包含字符串、64位整数或内存地址数据。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="538f6-444">Recognizer settings can contain string, 64-bit integer, or memory address data.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="538f6-445">下表描述了为符合 Microsoft Speech API （SAPI）的识别器定义的设置。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="538f6-445">The following table describes the settings that are defined for a Microsoft Speech API (SAPI)-compliant recognizer.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="538f6-446">对于支持设置的每个识别器，以下设置必须具有相同的范围。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="538f6-446">The following settings must have the same range for each recognizer that supports the setting.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="538f6-447">支持这些设置并可支持其他设置时，不需要使用 SAPI 兼容的识别器。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="538f6-447">A SAPI-compliant recognizer is not required to support these settings and can support other settings.</span></span>  
  
|<span data-ttu-id="538f6-448">name</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="538f6-448">Name</span></span>|<span data-ttu-id="538f6-449">说明</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="538f6-449">Description</span></span>|  
